race.comment: PALLADIUM (7) was good here on debut then a close-up fifth last time. Returns home and looks well placed out in journey. Should go close. Very wary of the well bred first starter MAKETIME (6). Gelding by Maurice and a half to dual Group 1 winner Magic Time. Well educated including a Flemington jump-out win most recently. Blinkers on and expected to measure up. PICK A SYMPHONY (3) is a former NSW galloper runner-up last two and now switches yards. Drawn to finish on strongly.  KINGTONDO (5) is a Flying Artie gelding who is making debut for the Freedman yard. Well educated and coming along nicely leading into this, most recently winning a Mornington jump-out. Expected to measure up.
